{"mentions":[],"message":"As Cutover Date (Actual) entered, the following automated actions has been completed:
1. Status updated from Ready for Cutover to Warranty.
2. Case "Stop Cutover Successfully Complete Email" flag has been ticked to stop this process to be triggered again when there is an update on the case.
3. Account Wireless Status is updated to "In Service" with the Cutover Date.
4. 7 days after cutover date automation has been registered."}

As Cutover Date (Actual) entered, the following automated actions has been completed: 1. Status updated from Ready for Cutover to Warranty. 2. Case "Stop Cutover Successfully Complete Email" flag has been ticked to stop this process to be triggered again when there is an update on the case. 3. Account Wireless Status is updated to "In Service" with the Cutover Date. 4. 7 days after cutover date automation has been registered.

value.stringValue:
{"mentions":[],"message":"As field "Cutover Appointment Confirmed" is ticked, the following automated actions have been completed:
1. Status is updated from Ready for Schedule to Appointment Confirmed.
2. The schedule/appointment confirmed email has been sent to the principal/case contact ({![Case].Contact.Email}) and IT Lead/case secondary contact if there is one. 
3. An inform email has also been sent to ICT Provider/ICT Implementer ({![Case].ICT_Implementation_Contact__r.Email}).
4. "Stop Appointment Confirmed Process " flag has been ticked to prevent this process to run again when there is an update on the case."}

As field "Cutover Appointment Confirmed" is ticked, the following automated actions have been completed: 1. Status is updated from Ready for Schedule to Appointment Confirmed. 2. The schedule/appointment confirmed email has been sent to the principal/case contact ({!myVariable_current.Contact.Email}) and IT Lead/case secondary contact if there is one. 3. An inform email has also been sent to ICT Provider/ICT Implementer ({!myVariable_current.ICT_Implementation_Contact__r.Email}). 4. "Stop Appointment Confirmed Process " flag has been ticked to prevent this process to run again when there is an update on the case.
